Data by Ernst Neufert, a German
architect, was published. Neufert dedicated his entire life to developing design
standards aimed at ensuring that people could live comfortably and efficiently in
the spaces they inhabited—a true focus on ergonomics. For instance, he
meticulously studied the ideal height and dimensions for stairs, tables, and even
a conveniently sized salt shaker for the table. He also analyzed the optimal
height for coat hooks to suit people of varying heights.
During his lifetime, Neufert established a foundation that facilitated the creation
of this handbook, which remains a cornerstone for architects and designers to
this day. The foundation, now over 100 years old, continues to operate, updating
and improving the handbook to adapt to modern needs.
